title: People's Market window lettering, Elko, Nevada: photographic print
body:
Exterior view of the People's Market in Elko, the earliest documented neon signs in NV. Detail shots included. Photos were taken during the day.

443 Idaho St, Elko, NV 89801
citation: NNN000001. Northern Nevada Neon, 1922-2021. Special Collections and Archives, University Libraries, University of Nevada, Las Vegas. Las Vegas, Nevada. http://n2t.net/ark:/62930/d16w9931n

title: Silver Dollar Club channel letters, Elko, Nevada: photographic print
body:
Exterior view of The Silver Dollar Club in Elko, NV, opened during the final weeks of the prohibition and closed its doors early 2020. Photographs provided are from different dates; the 1940's and 1986. Lit and unlit images featured.

Silver Dollar Club

title: Stockmen's Hotel channel letters, Elko, Nevada: photographic print
body:
Exterior view of The Stockmen's Hotel in Elko, NV. Photos from the 1940's and 1986. The images include views during the day with unlit neon and at night with lit neon.The present day site of the hotel used to be the Mayer Hotel.
